entries.meaning: (now rare) Relating to a member, in various senses; especially, (anatomy, zoology) pertaining to a limb.
examples: This man speakes of an unnaturall ill-favourdnesse and membrall deformity, but we call ill-favourdnesse a kinde of unseemelinesse at the first sight, which chiefely lodgeth in the face, and by the colour worketh a dislike in us.
